The Hazardous Material Endorsement is required to operate a vehicle transporting a hazardous material that is required to be placarded under the District of Columbia Hazardous Materials Transportation and Motor carrier Safety Act of 1988, effective
        March 16, 1989 (D.C. Law 7-190; D.C. Official Code § 8-1401 et seq.), or by the U.S. Secretary of Transportation in accordance with the Hazardous Material Transportation Act, approved January 3, 1975 (88 Stat. 2156; 49 U.S.C. § 1801 et seq. and
        49 CFR part 383, § 121);
